msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Gospel of John in Arabic missing the last verse.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

support.watermark: Crescent moon with face in profile in shield (Abū Shubbāk).

supportDesc.extent: 79 leaves : 126 x 84 (80 x 55) mm bound to 130 x 90 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper right verso; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

binding.p: Bound in brown textile over pasteboard; no spine; two sewing stations; modern label with manuscript identification and number adhered around spine between the sewing stations and extending onto both covers.

origin.p: The item is not dated, perhaps produced in the 19th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Cyrus Adler to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on library bookplate, inside back cover).
Likely formerly owned by Ibrāhīm ibn Yūsuf al-Rashīdī (somewhat effaced owner's note, f. 1r).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate inside back cover).
